UBS Committed to Investment Banking, Ermotti Tells SonntagsBlick

-- B y   R i c h a r d   W e i s s
-- 
2011-10-16T11:40:04Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-16/ubs-committed-to-investment-banking-ermotti-tells-sonntagsblick.html
UBS AG Interim Chief Executive
Officer  Sergio Ermotti  remains committed to investment banking,
 SonntagsBlick   reported, citing an interview with Ermotti.  40 percent of funds managed by UBS comes from clients with
personal wealth of 50 million Swiss francs ($56 million) or more
that use investment banking services, Ermotti told the Swiss
publication.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Richard Weiss in Frankfurt at 
